ocratic}} |53%\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |[[Sarah Palin]]\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |Republican\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |59,948,323<br/>173 electoral votes\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |46%\n|-\n|[[2012 United States presidential election|2012]]\n|General\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |65,915,796<br/>332 electoral votes (270 needed)\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |51%\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |[[Paul Ryan]]\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |Republican\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |60,933,500<br/>206 electoral votes\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |47%\n|}\n\n== Writings by Biden ==\n\n{{Refbegin}}\n* {{Cite book|url=https://www.amazon.com/Hague-Convention-International-Child-Abduction/dp/0756722500|title=Hague Convention On International Child Abduction: Applicable Law And Institutional Framework Within Certain Convention Countries Report To The Senate |last=Biden |first=Joseph R., Jr. |date=April 1, 2000|publisher=Diane Publishing|isbn=0-7567-2250-0|author2=Jesse Helms|author2-link=Jesse Helms}}\n* {{Cite book|url=http://frwebgate.access.gpo.gov/cgi-bin/getdoc.cgi?dbname=107_senate_hearings&docid=f:75011.pdf|title=Putin Administration's Policies toward Non-Russian Regions of the Russian Federation: Hearing before the Committee on Foreign Relations, U.S. Senate |last=Biden |first=Joseph R., Jr. |date=July 8, 2001|publisher=U.S. Government Printing Office|isbn= 0-7567-2624-7}}\n* {{Cite book|url=https://fas.org/spp/starwars/program/sfr240701.pdf|title=Administration's Missile Defense Program and the ABM Treaty: Hearing Before the Committee on Foreign Relations, U.S. Senate |last=Biden |first=Joseph R., Jr. |date=July 24, 2001|publisher=U.S. Government Printing Office|isbn=0-7567-1959-3|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305135604/https://fas.org/spp/starwars/program/sfr240701.pdf|archivedate=March 5, 2016}}\n* {{Cite book|url=http://frwebgate.access.gpo.gov/cgi-bin/getdoc.cgi?dbname=107_senate_hearings&docid=f:75040.p